The IP-XACT file is used to configure the pck600_lpd_p. The configuration options are:

SEQUENCER                :  Configures the lpd_p as a sequencer or expander. Its value is fetched from the yaml configuration file. Possible values are {0.1}. This maps to the SEQUENCER verilog parameter.

CTRL_P_CH_SYNC           :  Includes or excludes synchronizers on CTRL P-Channel. Its value is fetched from the yaml configuration file. Possible values are {0,1}. This maps to the CTRL_P_CH_SYNC verilog parameter.

DEV_P_CH_SYNC            :  Includes or excludes synchronizers on DEV P-Channel. Its value is fetched from the yaml configuration file. Possible values are {0,1}. This maps to the DEV_P_CH_SYNC verilog parameter.

DEV_P_CH_PREQ_DLY        :  Configures the number of clock cycles between Device PSTATE set and Device PREQ assertion. Its value is fetched from the yaml configuration file. Possible values are {0,1}. This maps to the DEV_P_CH_PREQ_DLY verilog parameter.

DEV_P_CH_<X>_SAME_EN     :  Configures whether or not a P-Channel request is issued when the PSATTE value is the same as the PSTATE that the component <X> is currently in. Its value is fetched from the yaml configuration file. Possible values are {0,1}. This maps to the DEV_P_CH_<X>_SAME_EN verilog parameter. <X> is the component P-Channel number.


